text: Washburn TownshipU.S. Geological Survey U.S. Board on Geographic Names information for Washburn Township is a township in Griggs County, North Dakota, United States. ==Demographics== Its population during the 2010 census was 68.North Dakota 2010 Census ==Location within Griggs County== Washburn Township is located in Township 146 Range 58 west of the Fifth principal meridian.Earth Point Tools for Google Earth {| class="wikitable" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; border: none;" |- || ! scope="col" | Range 61 ! scope="col" | Range 60 ! scope="col" | Range 59 ! scope="col" | Range 58 |- ! scope="col" | Township 148 | Rosendal | Willow | Pilot Mound | Lenora |- ! scope="col" | Township 147 | Bryan | Addie | Tyrol | Romness |- ! scope="col" | Township 146 | Kingsley | Clearfield | Cooperstown | style="background: yellow"|Washburn |- ! scope="col" | Township 145 | Mabel | Helena | Ball Hill | Sverdrup |- ! scope="col" | Township 144 | Dover | Bartley | Greenfield | Broadview |} ==References== :Category:Townships in Griggs County, North Dakota :Category:Townships in North Dakota Category:Townships in Griggs County, North Dakota
